# ============================================================================
# _gondolin — zsh completion for **gondolin** —
#            earendil-works/gondolin, the **Gondolin Agent
#            Sandbox** — a fast local-Linux micro-VM with
#            programmable network + filesystem control purpose-built
#            for **sandboxing AI-agent-generated code**.  Modern
#            (post-LLM-tool-call era) tool for the "AI agents
#            increasingly run generated code without human review;
#            that code often needs network access and credentials,
#            which creates exfiltration risk" problem domain.  Each
#            `gondolin bash` invocation spawns a QEMU micro-VM (or
#            optional libkrun backend on macOS Hypervisor.framework /
#            Linux KVM), boots an Alpine-based guest rootfs, mounts
#            the configured host filesystem paths, applies the
#            configured DNS + outbound-HTTP + outbound-SSH policy,
#            and drops the user into a shell inside the guest.
#            Host-side SSH proxy is implemented via **mscdex/ssh2**,
#            the canonical pure-JavaScript SSH 2.0 implementation
#            by Brian White.  TS-Node=182 **CLOSES** Axis 127 at
#            1/1/1 — triple-182 landmark (Rust=182 + Go=182 +
#            TS-Node=182) + 120th axis closed.
# ============================================================================
#
