# WHAT IT IS
#   Gondolin is the **AI-agent-code-execution sandbox VM** —
#   structurally positioned as:
#
#     • **Anthropic Computer Use sandbox alternative**     for
#       self-hosted Claude / Cursor / Cline / Aider / OpenAI
#       Code Interpreter-style local agent execution
#     • **Docker-in-Docker alternative**                   strong
#       isolation via hardware-virtualized micro-VM instead of
#       sharing the host kernel
#     • **gVisor alternative**                             same
#       use case (containerized untrusted workloads) but VM-
#       grade isolation with host-side network policy
#     • **Firecracker alternative**                        same
#       hardware-virtualization layer (KVM/Hypervisor.framework)
#       but with TS-native host orchestration instead of
#       Rust+Python
#     • **Daytona sandbox / E2B / CodeSandbox alternative** for
#       the self-hosted local-machine case
#
#   Architecture overview:
#
#     1. Host process (gondolin CLI, Node.js) spawns a QEMU or
#        libkrun micro-VM with virtio-vsock control channel
#     2. Guest boots from cached Alpine-based rootfs image
#     3. Host applies network policy:
#         - synthetic DNS / trusted DNS / open DNS modes
#         - outbound HTTP allow-list via MITM hook chain
#         - outbound SSH allow-list with host-side proxy using
#           **ssh2** (Brian White's library) for typed key
#           verification + agent forwarding + per-host
#           credential matching
#         - WebSocket upgrade enable/disable
#         - guest-host TCP port mappings (typed
#           `--tcp-map GUEST:UPSTREAM` spec)
#     4. Host injects placeholder secrets for the guest
#        (the real value is only revealed when an outbound
#        HTTP request matches the allow-listed host)
#     5. Host mounts host-FS paths via virtiofs
#     6. Host drops user into interactive shell OR runs
#        `gondolin exec <command>` headlessly
#     7. Optional VM checkpoint (`gondolin snapshot`) emits a
#        qcow2 disk image for `gondolin bash --resume` later
#
#   Subcommand surface:
#
#     • gondolin exec                  Run a command via the
#                                      virtio socket or in-
#                                      process VM
#     • gondolin bash                  Interactive shell in
#                                      sandbox (bash with sh
#                                      fallback;  Ctrl-] to
#                                      detach)
#     • gondolin list                  List active VM sessions
#     • gondolin attach <SESSION_ID>   Attach to running VM
#     • gondolin snapshot <SESSION_ID> Snapshot + stop a session
#     • gondolin build                 Build custom guest assets
#                                      (kernel + initramfs +
#                                      rootfs)
#     • gondolin image                 Manage local image refs +
#                                      objects
#     • gondolin help                  Show help
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `host/bin/gondolin.ts`
#                       hand-rolled CLI;  extracted via raw
#                       fetch of `host/bin/gondolin.ts`;  every
#                       flag below is a literal `console.log("
#                       --<flag-name> ...")` from the typed
#                       `usage()` / `bashUsage()` / `listUsage()`
#                       / `attachUsage()` / `snapshotUsage()` /
#                       `execUsage()` functions in the upstream
#                       source)
#
#   gondolin <COMMAND> [OPTIONS...] [-- COMMAND ARGS...]
#
#   `bash` + `exec` shared flags (Command + VFS + Network):
#     --cwd PATH                       working directory inside
#                                      guest
#     --env KEY=VALUE                  set guest env var
#                                      (repeatable)
#     --resume ID_OR_PATH              resume from a snapshot
#                                      ID (matched against
#                                      `~/.cache/gondolin/
#                                      checkpoints/`) or
#                                      absolute .qcow2 path
#     --image IMAGE                    guest image selector:
#                                      asset dir / build id /
#                                      `name:tag`
#     --vmm BACKEND                    VM backend: `qemu` |
#                                      `krun` (default: qemu)
#     --rootfs-size SIZE               ensure rootfs virtual
#                                      disk is at least SIZE
#                                      (e.g. `8G`)
#     --mount-hostfs HOST:GUEST[:ro]   mount host directory at
#                                      guest path (`:ro`
#                                      suffix for read-only)
#     --mount-memfs PATH               memory-backed mount at
#                                      guest path
#     --allow-host HOST                allow outbound HTTP to
#                                      host (repeatable)
#     --host-secret NAME@HOST[,HOST...][=VALUE]
#                                      add secret for hosts;
#                                      if `=VALUE` omitted,
#                                      reads from $NAME
#     --dns MODE                       `synthetic` | `trusted`
#                                      | `open` (default
#                                      `synthetic`)
#     --dns-trusted-server IP          trusted resolver IPv4
#                                      (repeatable)
#     --dns-synthetic-host-mapping M   synthetic DNS mapping:
#                                      `single` | `per-host`
#     --tcp-map SPEC                   GUEST_HOST[:PORT]=
#                                      UPSTREAM_HOST:PORT
#     --ssh-allow-host HOST[:PORT]     allow outbound SSH to
#                                      host (repeatable;
#                                      default port 22)
#     --ssh-agent [SOCK]               use ssh-agent for
#                                      host-side SSH auth
#                                      (defaults to
#                                      $SSH_AUTH_SOCK)
#     --ssh-known-hosts PATH           OpenSSH known_hosts
#                                      for upstream
#                                      verification
#                                      (repeatable)
#     --ssh-credential SPEC            HOST[:PORT]=PATH or
#                                      USER@HOST[:PORT]=PATH;
#                                      optional `,passphrase-
#                                      env=ENV` or
#                                      `,passphrase=...`
#     --disable-websockets             disable WebSocket
#                                      upgrades (egress +
#                                      ingress)
#
#   `bash`-only ingress + debugging:
#     --listen [HOST:PORT]             start host ingress
#                                      gateway (default
#                                      `127.0.0.1:0`)
#     --ssh                            enable SSH access via
#                                      localhost port forward
#     --ssh-user USER                  SSH username
#                                      (default `root`)
#     --ssh-port PORT                  local listen port
#                                      (default `0` =
#                                      ephemeral)
#     --ssh-listen HOST                local listen host
#                                      (default `127.0.0.1`)
#
#   `list`:
#     --all                            include stale/dead
#                                      sessions
#
#   `snapshot`:
#     --output PATH                    absolute/relative path
#                                      for the snapshot
#                                      .qcow2
#     --name NAME                      snapshot name
#
#   `exec` (sock mode):
#     --sock PATH                      virtio sock path
#     --cmd CMD                        command (repeatable)
#     --arg ARG                        arg for last --cmd
#                                      (repeatable)
#
#   Global:
#     --help, -h                       show help
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `earendil-works/gondolin`'s `host/package.json` declares a
#   **direct** dependency on `ssh2@^1.17.0`.  The
#   `host/src/ssh/` workspace member implements the typed
#   outbound-SSH allow-list policy + the host-side SSH proxy
#   for guest-originating SSH connections, using typed
#   `import { Client, ParsedKey, parseKey, utils } from
#   "ssh2"` and typed `new Client()` /  typed `client.connect({
#   host, port, username, privateKey, passphrase, agent,
#   hostHash, hostVerifier, algorithms })`.  Outbound SSH
#   requests from the guest VM hit the typed host-side proxy,
#   which inspects the requested host against the configured
#   typed `sshAllowedHosts` array, looks up the matching typed
#   `sshCredentials` (private key, ssh-agent, or
#   keyboard-interactive auth), and proxies the raw SSH 2.0
#   handshake through to the upstream — providing typed
#   policy + audit + secret-injection across the SSH boundary
#   the same way the typed HTTP `httpHooks` do for HTTP.
#
#   **mscdex/ssh2** (`ssh2` on npm) is **THE canonical pure-
#   JavaScript SSH 2.0 implementation** — Brian White's
#   (mscdex on GitHub) reference pure-JS implementation of the
#   entire SSH 2.0 protocol stack (RFC 4250 + RFC 4251 +
#   RFC 4252 + RFC 4253 + RFC 4254 + RFC 4256 + RFC 4419 +
#   RFC 4716 + RFC 5656 + RFC 8268 + RFC 8308 + RFC 8332 +
#   RFC 8709 + RFC 8731 + RFC 9142).  In active development
#   since 2012 with 5,800+ ★ on github.com/mscdex/ssh2.
#   Clocks **4 million weekly downloads on npm** — the
#   dominant Node-side SSH library by 2+ orders of magnitude
#   vs alternatives like `simple-ssh` (thin wrapper over
#   ssh2), `node-ssh` (wrapper), `ssh2-promise` (Promise-
#   based wrapper over ssh2), or shelling out to system
#   `ssh` (defeats the purpose of using Node).
#
#   ssh2 ships:
#
#     • Typed `Client`                 typed client constructor
#                                      with typed
#                                      `Client.connect({
#                                      host, port, username,
#                                      password, privateKey,
#                                      passphrase, agent,
#                                      agentForward, tryKeyboard,
#                                      hostHash, hostVerifier,
#                                      readyTimeout, keepalive*,
#                                      algorithms,
#                                      authHandler,
#                                      strictVendor,
#                                      identity, ident,
#                                      forceIPv4, forceIPv6,
#                                      localAddress,
#                                      localPort,
#                                      sock, debug })`
#     • Typed `Server`                 typed
#                                      `Server({hostKeys,
#                                      algorithms, ident,
#                                      banner, greeting,
#                                      identity, debug,
#                                      highWaterMark})` server
#                                      constructor for typed
#                                      SSH 2.0 server
#                                      implementations
#     • Typed `Session`                typed channel for
#                                      typed shell + exec +
#                                      env + pty + signal +
#                                      window-change +
#                                      x11 + agent +
#                                      subsystem requests
#     • Typed SFTP                     typed `client.sftp()`
#                                      → typed `SFTPWrapper`
#                                      with typed
#                                      `readDir`, `readFile`,
#                                      `writeFile`, `stat`,
#                                      `lstat`, `fstat`,
#                                      `mkdir`, `rmdir`,
#                                      `unlink`, `rename`,
#                                      `symlink`,
#                                      `readlink`, `realpath`,
#                                      `chmod`, `chown`,
#                                      `setstat`, `fsetstat`,
#                                      `open`, `close`,
#                                      `write`, `read`,
#                                      `createReadStream`,
#                                      `createWriteStream`,
#                                      `fastGet`, `fastPut`
#                                      typed methods
#     • Typed key-exchange algorithms  typed concrete:
#                                      curve25519-sha256
#                                      (RFC 8731), curve25519-
#                                      sha256@libssh.org,
#                                      ecdh-sha2-nistp256/
#                                      384/521, diffie-hellman-
#                                      group14-sha256/sha1,
#                                      diffie-hellman-
#                                      group16-sha512,
#                                      diffie-hellman-
#                                      group18-sha512,
#                                      diffie-hellman-
#                                      group-exchange-sha256
#     • Typed cipher algorithms        typed concrete:
#                                      chacha20-poly1305@
#                                      openssh.com,
#                                      aes256-gcm@openssh.com,
#                                      aes128-gcm@openssh.com,
#                                      aes256-ctr,
#                                      aes192-ctr,
#                                      aes128-ctr
#     • Typed MAC algorithms           typed concrete:
#                                      hmac-sha2-256-etm@
#                                      openssh.com,
#                                      hmac-sha2-512-etm@
#                                      openssh.com,
#                                      hmac-sha2-256,
#                                      hmac-sha2-512,
#                                      hmac-sha1
#     • Typed public-key auth          typed
#                                      `parseKey(rawKey,
#                                      passphrase)` parser for
#                                      PEM / OpenSSH /
#                                      PKCS#8 / PPK encoded
#                                      private keys
#     • Typed ssh-agent forwarding     typed `agent` socket
#                                      path or typed
#                                      `BaseAgent` impl
#                                      (`OpenSSHAgent`,
#                                      `PageantAgent`,
#                                      `CygwinAgent`,
#                                      `HTTPAgent`)
#     • Typed direct-tcpip + direct-
#       streamlocal forwarding         typed
#                                      `client.forwardOut(srcIP,
#                                      srcPort, destIP,
#                                      destPort)` + typed
#                                      `client.openssh_forwardOutStreamLocal(
#                                      socketPath)`
#     • Typed forwarded-tcpip remote
#       port-forward                   typed
#                                      `client.forwardIn(remoteAddr,
#                                      remotePort)` +
#                                      typed
#                                      `client.openssh_forwardInStreamLocal(
#                                      socketPath)`
#     • Typed X11 forwarding
#     • Typed PTY                      typed
#                                      `session.pty(rows,
#                                      cols, modes)`
#     • Typed signal + window-change   typed
#                                      `session.signal()` /
#                                      `session.windowChange()`
#     • Typed compression              typed
#                                      `zlib@openssh.com`
#     • Typed certificate auth         typed OpenSSH SSH
#                                      certificate format
#     • Typed connection-rekeying      typed periodic + on-
#                                      demand rekey
#     • Typed banner support           typed pre-auth banner
#                                      callback
#     • Native C++ ssh2-streams binding
#       for fast crypto                via the bundled
#                                      `cpu-features` +
#                                      `ssh2-streams` native
#                                      addon (with pure-JS
#                                      fallback)
#
#   ssh2 is the SSH library behind essentially every modern
#   Node.js / Electron / browser-extension SSH-aware
#   application:
#
#     • **microsoft/vscode** — the typed `vscode-remote-ssh`
#       extension's Node bootstrap uses ssh2 internally for
#       the typed handshake + key-verification path
#     • **n8n** (50,000+ ★) — the workflow automation
#       platform's typed SSH node uses ssh2
#     • **electerm** (16,000+ ★) — the open-source cross-
#       platform terminal Electron app (the Hyper / iTerm /
#       Tabby competitor with built-in SSH/SFTP)
#     • **luin/medis** (12,000+ ★) — the Redis GUI app uses
#       ssh2 for the typed SSH-tunnel mode
#     • **Subash/Prepros** — frontend build tool with
#       typed SSH deploy
#     • **redis/RedisInsight** — Redis's official GUI uses
#       ssh2 for SSH-tunneled Redis connections
#     • **billchurch/webssh2** — the canonical browser-side
#       WebSocket-to-SSH gateway
#     • **livecycle/preevy** — the ephemeral-environment
#       preview platform
#     • **simstudioai/sim** — AI workflow simulator
#     • **looker-open-source/actions** — Looker Action
#       Hub SSH actions
#     • **democratic-csi/democratic-csi** — Kubernetes
#       CSI driver for democratic storage backends
#     • **jeroenpeeters/docker-ssh** — Docker container
#       SSH gateway
#     • **whxaxes/blog** — blog SSH deploy
#     • **lucasmotta/dploy** — Node SFTP deploy
#     • **idletoaster/ssh-mcp-server** — SSH MCP server
#       for LLM-driven SSH-host operations
#     • **earendil-works/gondolin** (this very project)
#     • **sanketbajoria/ssh2-promise** — the Promise-based
#       sugar wrapper over ssh2 itself
#     • Plus thousands of internal Node SSH-aware backends.
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/earendil-works/gondolin/contents/host/
#                                                  package.json
#       → "name": "@earendil-works/gondolin"
#       → "bin": { "gondolin": "./dist/bin/gondolin.js" }
#       → "dependencies": { ..., "ssh2": "^1.17.0", ... }
